articles.author: Steve Holland, Matt Spetalnick, Jeff Mason
articles.description: President Donald Trump vowed on Tuesday that the U.S. would take over the war-ravaged Gaza Strip after Palestinians are resettled elsewhere and develop it economically, a move that would shatter decades of U.S. policy toward the Israeli-Palestinian conflict.
articles.title: Trump, in shock announcement, says U.S. wants to take over Gaza Strip

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Saudi Arabia said on Wednesday it would not establish ties with Israel without the creation of a Palestinian state - a statement that comes after U.S. President Donald Trump said that the Saudis were not demanding a Palestinian state.
articles.title: Saudi Arabia says it won't establish ties with Israel without creation of Palestinian state

articles.author: Humeyra Pamuk
articles.description: The U.S. State Department has ordered the shutdown of overseas missions of U.S. Agency for International Development and is working to recall thousands of staff worldwide, two sources familiar with the discussions said on Tuesday.
articles.title: State Dept orders shutdown of USAID overseas missions, recalls staff, sources say

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Swedish police said on Tuesday five people were shot in an attack at a school for adults in the city of Orebro some 200 km (125 miles) west of Stockholm, triggering a massive response by rescue services.
articles.title: Five people shot in attack at Swedish school, police say

articles.author: Steve Holland, Jeff Mason
articles.description: U.S. President Donald Trumpon Tuesday restored his "maximum pressure" campaign on Iran that includes efforts to drive its oil exports down to zero in order to stop Tehran from obtaining a nuclear weapon.
articles.title: Trump reimposes 'maximum pressure' on Iran, aims to drive oil exports to zero

articles.author: Trevor Hunnicutt, Kevin Huang
articles.description: China on Tuesday slapped tariffs on U.S. imports in a rapid response to new U.S. duties on Chinese goods, renewing a trade war between the world's top two economies as President Donald Trump sought to punish China for not halting the flow of illicit drugs.
articles.title: China hits back with tariffs on US goods after Trump imposes new levies

articles.author: Kirsty Needham
articles.description: Gender equality will become central to Australia's foreign policy, diplomacy, trade and aid programmers under a new international strategy, Foreign Minister Penny Wong said on Wednesday in Canberra.
articles.title: Australia makes gender equality key to foreign policy and aid

articles.author: John Revill
articles.description: The Aga Khan, known for his triumphs in horse racing, dazzling wealth and development work around the world, has died in Lisbon at the age of 88, according to the Aga Khan Development Network on X.
articles.title: The Aga Khan, spiritual leader whose riches enabled horse racing glory, dies at 88

articles.author: Bing Lok
articles.description: Singapore has passed a law designed to protect against foreign interference in its race-based clans and business associations, as the government looks to limit outsiders from undermining racial harmony in the multicultural city-state.
articles.title: Singapore passes law against foreign interference in race-based organisations

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A magnitude 6.2 earthquake struck off the coast of Indonesia's North Maluku on Wednesday, the geophysics agency said.
articles.title: Magnitude 6.2 quake hits offshore of Indonesia's North Maluku
